snippet.textDisplay: Honestly a flat dense brush has never worked for me to put on any metallic shades. When people get mad at palettes for “not working” with a flat synthetic brush it makes no sense to me because a flat synthetic brush doesn’t pick up any product. I can’t be the only one? Who decided all metallics need to work with a dense flat brush?

snippet.textDisplay: just trying to put it out there, someone said "no disrespect at all -  but MLM & Pyramid Schemes are two different things. (and, No, I am NOT part of an MLM) . A pyramid Scheme is an actual scam that would take money from un-suspecting consumers to just recruit others to their "service" and make a cut of their recruitment. True, an MLM & Pyramid Scheme are both built on the business model of "multiple levels" of distributors and recruits, however, MLM's focus on recruiting salespeople to move & sell product - there is actual value and you don't necessarily make money on your recruit sign ups (like a pyramid scheme) - you make money off your team's sales." and its true. personally, I agree MANY MLM companies aren't the best, but the ones that I've seen (ive never been involved in one personally, although I have friends that are starting one right now) it's definitely about the customers, it's not as simple as im gonna recruit people and sell product, but it's definitely not a pyramid scheme.
